% If you employ 5 or more people, you must keep a written record of your risk assessment.%

You don't have to record your risk assessment in any particular way, but you can make it easier by using the Health and Safety Executive's (HSE):

- online risk assessment tool for [offices](http://www.hse.gov.uk/risk/office.htm "Risk assessment tool for offices"){:rel="external"} or [shops](http://www.hse.gov.uk/risk/shop.htm "Risk assessment tool for shops"){:rel="external"} 
- [examples](http://www.hse.gov.uk/risk/casestudies/index.htm "Example health and safety risk assessments"){:rel="external"}

You can download a risk assessment template from the HSE.

$D

[Download a risk assessment template (DOC, 111KB)](http://www.hse.gov.uk/risk/risk-assessment-and-policy-template.doc "Download a health and safety risk assessment template (Word document, 111KB"){:rel="external"}

$D

*[HSE]: Health and Safety Executive
